cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on local feature detection in computer vision, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a generic framework based on improved repeatability measure, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of detectors under different conditions, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
